	</meta_data>
	<paragraph>
		<paragraph>Many operations in EiffelBuild do not require the use of the mouse. The same effect can be achieved through the keyboard only.</paragraph>
		<paragraph>This page gathers all the keyboard shortcuts available in the environment.</paragraph>
		<heading>
			<size>2</size>Key shortcut reference 
		</heading>
		<table>
			<row>
				<cell>
					<bold>Key shortcut</bold>
				</cell>
				<cell>
					<bold>action</bold>
				</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>
					<italic>- file shortcuts -</italic>
				</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Ctrl+O</cell>
				<cell>Open project.</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Ctrl+N</cell>
				<cell>New Project.</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Ctrl+S</cell>
				<cell>Save project</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>
					<italic>- code generation shortcuts -</italic>
				</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Ctrl+G</cell>
				<cell>Generate code from project.</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>
					<italic>- miscellaneous shortcuts -</italic>
				</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Delete</cell>
				<cell>Delete object from currently selected tool.</cell>
			</row>
			<row>
				<cell>Ctrl+T</cell>
				<cell>Tool always on top.</cell>
			</row>
		</table>
		<paragraph>
			<bold>Note</bold>: These shortcuts are not always available and are dependent on the state of EiffelBuild. For example, Ctrl+S does nothing if there is no modified project open. 
		</paragraph>
